Why two processes
-----------------

The GPL-3.0 daemon hosts the WolvenKit libraries so the MIT-licensed MCP server
never links them and stays outside the copyleft. The `.mcpb` bundle ships both
the server and the daemon; per the project's licensing stance, the bundle's
manifest license reflects the most restrictive component present (GPL-3.0).